Class PoliceBookingSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pbs.controller.PoliceBookingSystem

  • @RestController
 @RequestMapping(value="api/v1/")
public class PoliceBookingSystem
extends java.lang.Object
    Created by Michael Collins on 27/04/2017. The main class within the system. It is concerned with connect all of the other classes together, and ensuring that they have the ability to contact each other when required. It allows the front end to "talk to" the back end

      • update

        @RequestMapping(value="reports/{id}/no_action",
                method=PUT)
public Report update(@PathVariable
                                                                                                   java.lang.Integer id,
                                                                                                   @RequestBody
                                                                                                   NoAction report)
        These methods are the update methods for the system When a user has edited a currently existing report, it is passed back to the ReportController, which then executes the updateReport method in ReportStub. The reason that there are four different update links being supplied is due to the fact that each method passes back a different type of report, this lets us get all of the individual details that are specific to that report, rather than saving it as a generic Report and losing all of the attributes specific to that report type.
